24 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 12, Chapter 9, Subchapter 1, is amended
25 to add an additional section to read as follows:
26 12-9-127. Psychological evaluations or assessments.
27 (a) The Arkansas Commission on Law Enforcement Standards and Training
28 shall require all individuals to be evaluated or assessed by a licensed
29 psychiatrist or psychologist before employment with a law enforcement agency.
30 (b) A law enforcement officer employed by a law enforcement agency,
31 regardless of whether employed full time, part time, or on an auxiliary
32 basis, shall be evaluated or assessed every five (5) years by an individual
33 licensed to practice psychiatry or psychology and qualified to perform a
34 psychological evaluation or assessment in this state.
35 (c) A psychological evaluation or assessment under this section may be
36 conducted in-person or through telemedicine.
